-- Square Enix Says It Starts Offering Facebook Games; Shares Pare Declines
-- B y   Y o s h i n o r i   E k i
-- 2010-11-02T04:57:15Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-02/square-enix-says-it-starts-offering-facebook-games-shares-pare-declines.html
Square Enix Holdings Co., the
Japanese games developer, began offering titles geared for
Facebook Inc.’s online social-networking service.  The company began offering "Chocobo’s Crystal Tower" and
"Knights of the Crystals" for Facebook users, Square Enix said
today in an e-mailed statement. They’re Square Enix’s first
Facebook games, said Misa Tokunaga, a spokeswoman at the
Japanese company.  Square Enix fell 2.6 percent to 1,629 yen at 1:52 p.m. in
Tokyo, paring an earlier decline of as much as 6.8 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Yoshinori Eki in Tokyo at 
 yeki@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
